<TITLE> More road shows this month to woo FDI in power </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)The Power Development Board hopes to woo foreign funds in the two road shows in Singapore and USA this month arranged into the cash-trapped power and energy sector. A PDB official said on Tuesday the first one will be held at Pan Pacific Hotel, Singapore on Jan 25 and the other will take place on Jan 28-29 at the Marriott Marquis Hotel of Time Square in New York, USA. The events are scheduled to include road show conferences and one-on-one discussions with the potential investors of USA, the official told bdnews24.com on condition of anonymity. On Dec15-16, Bangladesh organised the first show of this kind in London where a proposal for generating 3,900 megawatt electricity -- 2600 MW by coal and 1300 MW by gas -- was made. With these shows, the government aims to draw foreign direct investments in its proposed coal-based and dual fuel projects, the official added.
